
Todays Soft Skill Tip:

Day 19 – Professional Email Writing: Your Digital First Impression

Your emails speak for you - even when you’re not there. A good email is short, polite, and clear.
Professional tone shows respect, attention, and clarity of thought.
The best communicators don’t write long - they write right.

Task:
Write one professional email today using this structure:
⦁  Greeting (Dear/Hello)
⦁  Purpose (Reason for writing)
⦁  Gratitude (Thank you / Appreciate your time)

